                  sexual maturity (from 4 to 6 months of age) will prevent
                  unwanted pregnancies as well as reduce roaming behaviour and
                  territorial marking. Allowing your cat to roam outdoors prior
                  to desexing will increase their likelihood of falling
                  pregnant.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <b>
                    Fun Fact:
