                  months of age, although in some cases kittens can be desexed
                  as early as 8 to 16 weeks depending on the size and breed of
                  the cat. RSPCA Australia supports early age desexing as an
                  effective way to reduce unwanted pregnancies and rehome cats
                  as soon as possible.
                </p>

